category: SOME LAZY WORDS
category comment: 

clue: There's a shell-less mollusk at the start of this word meaning slow & lazy

response: sluggish

clue: The mid-1800s gave us this hyphenated word for an employee who keeps a close eye on the hour & minute hands

response: a clock-watcher

clue: Oscitant is an adjective that means doing this--& don't start, because I will too

response: yawning

clue: A prefix meaning "bad" begins this word for  feigning illness in order to avoid work

response: malingering

clue: Meaning inert or drowsy, it comes from Greek for "forget", like the name of a mythological river

response: lethargic

